    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Previous names",
            "shortText": "<p><i>Zygophyllum morgsana</i></p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_9_9743",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Rounded perennial shrub with jointed stems. Leaves succulent and emerge from stems as paired, rounded leaflets. Flowers small, pale-yellow with four petals, each with small reddish marking at base. Large, abundant fruits are reddish, elongate and each have four conspicuous wings.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_9744",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Typically reaches a height of about 2 m. Fruits about 15 mm wide.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_9745",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to Southern Africa.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> Namibia to Eastern Cape.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_9746",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Common on sandy and stony slopes mostly along the coast, but also extending well inland. Typically in arid conditions. Species in this genus are often grazed by stock.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_9747",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_9748",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Flowers April to October.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_9749",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>A large genus containing about 50 species, of which about 20 occur in the fynbos region. Among the larger shrub-like species most likely to be confused with Thin twinleaf <i>R. flexuosa</i>, which occurs along the coast in the South Western and southern Cape. However, the flowers of that species have five petals and the fruit are globular, wider than long and have five rather than four wings.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_9750",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        }
    ],
